godb/arangodb\",\n      \"path\": \"arangod/Aql/Optimizer.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Optimizer\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"arangodb/arangodb\",\n      \"path\": \"arangod/Aql/ExecutionEngine.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ExecutionEngine\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"arangodb/arangodb\",\n      \"path\": \"arangod/Aql/ExecutionBlock.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ExecutionBlock\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"arangodb/arangodb\",\n      \"path\": \"arangod/RocksDBEngine/RocksDBCollection.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"RocksDBCollection\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"arangodb/arangodb\",\n      \"path\": \"arangod/Transaction/Manager.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Manager\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The AQL query execution pipeline in ArangoDB follows this flow: (1) **Parsing**: The query string is parsed by the Parser class in arangod/Aql/Parser.cpp, which tokenizes and builds an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST). (2) **Optimization**: The Optimizer class in arangod/Aql/Optimizer.cpp transforms the AST into an optimized execution plan by applying various optimization rules. (3) **Execution Planning and Execution**: The ExecutionEngine class in arangod/Aql/ExecutionEngine.cpp instantiates and orchestrates the execution of ExecutionBlocks. ExecutionBlock in arangod/Aql/ExecutionBlock.cpp is the base class for various execution nodes that process data through the pipeline. (4) **Data Retrieval**: When the execution engine needs to fetch data from collections, it uses the RocksDBCollection class in arangod/RocksDBEngine/RocksDBCollection.cpp, which provides the storage engine interface for document retrieval and scanning through RocksDB. (5) **Transaction Management**: The query execution runs within a transaction context managed by the Manager class in arangod/Transaction/Manager.cpp, with transaction operations exposed through the Methods class in arangod/Transaction/Methods.cpp. These five key components work together to parse, optimize, and execute AQL queries against the underlying RocksDB storage engine.\"\n}\n",
